kids\', \'https://www.chess.com/blog/Steakanator/winners-pov-breslau-1889\': \'Title: Winner\\\'s POV: Breslau 1889 - Chess.com\\nDescription: May 20, 2025 ... ... Leipzig 1877 tournament (the celebrated "Anderssen Jubilee"). Anyone ... Szymon Winawer - Wilhelm Steinitz, 1882. Drawn in round 29 of\\xa0...\\nLong Description: In Winner\\\'s POV, we take a look at tournaments from the 19th century and see the games that allowed the top player to prevail. Some tournaments will be known and famous, others will be more obscure - in a time period where competition is scarce, I believe there is some value in digging for hidden gems...\', \'https://en.chessbase.com/post/an-adolf-anderssen-anniversary\': \'Title: An Adolf Anderssen anniversary | ChessBase\\nDescription: Mar 13, 2019 ... The tournament took place in May 1851 in the knockout system and is ... Wilhelm Steinitz in the first official competition for the\\xa0...\\nLong Description: In addition to Lasker\\\'s 150th birthday, the German chess had another anniversary to celebrate last year. On July 6, 1818, 200 years ago, Adolf Anderssen was born in Breslau. After his victory in London in 1851, he was considered the best player in the world. He died 140 years ago today, on March 13, 1879. Replay his "Evergreen Game" with notes by Garry Kasparov! | Photo: German Chess Federation\'}}', 'tool_call_id': 'call_8M4wjzscO1RUScDN9Bi3X2ES'}, {'role': 'assistant', 'content': '', 'tool_calls': [{'id': 'call_8NYaKulXmmNR0sl3nO2PvmPz', 'type': 'function', 'function': {'name': 'select_query_and_search', 'arguments': '{"query": "Leipzig 1877 chess tournament history", "enhanced_query": "\\"Leipzig 1877\\" AND \\"chess tournament\\" AND history"}'}}]}, {'role': 'tool', 'content': '{\'search_results\': {\'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adolf_Anderssen\': \'Title: Adolf Anderssen - Wikipedia\\nDescription: ... chess tournament. He achieved most of these successes when he was over the ... The Leipzig 1877 tournament was organised in his