tanding ...\\nDescription: One of ever-bestsellers in chess \'Zurich international chess tournament 1953\' by world famous David Bronstein. ... Der Schachkongreß Leipzig 1877. Reprint\\xa0...\\nLong Description: N/A", \'https://www.scribd.com/document/546936683/HighlightBooks\': "Title: Books: David Delucia Collection Highlights of The Chess Library | PDF\\nDescription: Lucena\'s dedication of his book to Prince John of Spain, the son of ... Leipzig 1877 chess tournament: Schallopp, Leipzig, 1878. Nuova Rivista degli\\xa0...\\nLong Description: The document summarizes highlights from David DeLucia\'s chess library collection, including some of the rarest books on chess in existence. It describes early chess manuals from the 15th-16th centuries, including the earliest known manual from 1496-97 by Lucena and rare editions by Damiano from 1512 and 1524. It also notes a 1525 book by Vida of which only three copies are known to exist and manuscripts such as the Paris Manuscript owned by DeLucia, considered one of the most sophisticated works on chess strategy. There has been scholarly debate about whether the Göttingen Manuscript or Lucena\'s book is the oldest analysis of modern chess play.", \'https://anyflip.com/wueey/intf/basic\': \'Title: THE PENGUIN ENCYCLOPEDIA OF CHESS - Flip eBook Pages 1 ...\\nDescription: Jan 20, 2022 ... Leipzig 1877. Anderssen may be regarded as the first great ... See under hooooven chess tournament. 39. BHEND, Edwin (b. 9 September\\xa0...\\nLong Description: N/A\', \'https://timenote.info/en/Adolf-Anderssen\': \'Title: Adolf Anderssen\\nDescription: ... chess tournament, considered comparable in the strength of its contestants ... The Leipzig 1877 tournament, in which Anderssen came second behind Louis\\xa0...\\nLong Description: Karl Ernst Adolf Anderssen (July 6, 1818 – March 13, 1879) was a German chess master.\', \'https://ebin.pub/on-the-origin-of-good-moves-a-skeptics-guide-at-getting-better-at-chess-9056918796-9789056918798.html\':